beer.beer_description: This DDH Pale is an extremely easy drinking hazy pale ale. With a light malt bill consisting predominantly of pale malt with a tiny hit of caramunich, it is a beautiful light orange colour with a soft haze. It has upfront aromas of citrus with a strong hint of rockmelon and cantaloupe to finish. On the palate is a medium and velvety body which carries the luscious notes of rockmelon and light citrus perfectly. The finish is dry and crisp and will leave you longing for another sip.
